<title>USA: Bayer acquires iron oxide distributor.</title>
<headline>Bayer acquires iron oxide distributor.</headline>
<dateline>PITTSBURGH 1996-10-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bayer Corp said on Thursday that it has concluded negotiations to acquire the iron oxide business of  Landers Segal Color Inc of Passaic, N.J.</p>
<p>The Bayer AG unit said the asset-based acquisition includes the blending, marketing and distribution operations for synthetic and natural iron oxide products. Bayer's Bayferrox iron oxide pigments are manufactured in New Martinsville, W. Va., and Uerdingen, Germany.</p>
<p>Landers Segal, which has represented Bayer's Bayferrox iron oxide pigments for over 25 years, is a nationwide pigments distributing company.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.</p>
